<HEADLINE> Astros 10, Padres 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Jeff Bagwell hit a grand slam and Shane
Reynolds hit a solo home run and pitched five effective innings to
lead the Houston Astros to a 10-4 win Friday night over the San
Diego Padres.
</P>
<P>
   Bagwell homered off Kevin Walker to cap a six-run, sixth inning
as the Astros broke a 3-3 tie. Walker was making his major league
debut.
</P>
<P>
   Reynolds (2-0) was not at his sharpest as he allowed three runs
and 10 hits in five innings. But the right-hander was able to pitch
out of trouble to keep the score close.
</P>
<P>
   Reynolds was more successful with his bat as he hit a solo homer
off Brian Boehringer (0-2) leading off the fifth inning to tie the
game.
</P>
<P>
   Houston then took control in the sixth. Moises Alou led off with
a single, knocking Boehringer from the game. Billy Spiers followed
with an RBI double off Will Cunnane and Tony Eusebio had an RBI
single.
</P>
<P>
   After a two-out walk to Craig Biggio, Walker entered the game
and walked Roger Cedeno to load the bases. Bagwell then lined a 2-2
fastball over the right-field wall. It was his 15th career home run
at Qualcomm Stadium, the most he's had in any visiting park.
</P>
<P>
   Boehringer gave the Padres a 3-2 lead in the fourth with a
two-run double over the head of Alou in right field.
</P>
<P>
   The Astros went ahead 2-1 in the second on Alou's home run and a
sacrifice fly by Tim Bogar.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Alou left the game in the sixth inning with a tight left
calf. ... The Padres continue to play without injured OFs Tony
Gwynn (sore knee) and Ruben Rivera (wrist). Gwynn missed his fourth
straight game after having his left knee drained Monday. Rivera has
not started the last five games. ... Astros 3B Ken Caminiti
(strained left hamstring) sat out his fourth straight start,
although he might be ready to play Saturday. ... Reynolds has won
10 of 15 career starts vs. San Diego. ... Houston's Matt Mieske
(lower back strain) was activated from the 15-day DL. ... RHP Scott
Elarton is scheduled to make his first start of the season for
Houston on Tuesday at Los Angeles. Elarton, who began the season on
the DL as he recovered from offseason rotator cuff surgery.
</P>
