<HEADLINE> Judge overturns animal cruelty conviction of E.Brunswickveterinarian  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW BRUNSWICK, N.J. (AP) -- A state Superior Court judge has
thrown out the criminal convictions of an East Brunswick
veterinarian accused of killing and abusing pets in his care.
</P>
<P>
   Howard Baker had been fined $3,500 and ordered to perform
community service last July after being convicted in Old Bridge
municipal court of animal cruelty against 11 pets. His conviction
was based on the testimony of an animal rights activist who worked
undercover in his office.
</P>
<P>
   Baker's license had also been revoked by a state veterinary
board, and Friday's court ruling had no immediate affect on that
decision. He had been a practicing veterinarian for two years and
operated the Village Veterinary Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Superior Court Judge Joyce Munkacsi said the municipal charges
against Baker were not supported by credible evidence and she said
the chief witness against Baker was biased.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Salvato, a spokeswoman for the state Board of
Veterinary Medical Examiners, said the board may conduct
independent hearings to determine whether Baker's license should be
reinstated. Lawyer Michael Rosenbaum said Friday the board has ''no
choice but to overturn'' its decision.
</P>
<P>
   The allegations against Baker were brought to local prosecutors
by Michele Rokke, a former activist and investigator for People for
the Ethical Treatment of Animals who made secret videotapes of
Baker while employed at his clinic as an assistant from June 1996
to April 1997.
</P>
<P>
   At his trial, Baker admitted giving light slaps or taps to pets,
and grabbing cats by the scruff of the neck to settle them down,
but he denied the cruelty charges.
</P>
<P>
   Baker's trial lawyer had argued Rokke was an ''animal rights
zealot whose lack of training or experience in the conduct of
veterinary medicine and radical views taint her perception of
events involving animals.''
</P>
<P>
   As he left court Friday, Baker said, ''Where do I go to get my
reputation back?''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
