<HEADLINE> Jordan Seizes $10M of Heroin  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AMMAN, Jordan (AP) -- Customs officers have seized heroin with a
street value of $10.5 million in Jordan's largest-ever catch of the
drug, the official Petra news agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The officers found the 235 pounds of heroin in a foreign truck
at the Al-Jaber crossing on the Syrian border, Petra said. The
crossing is 24 miles north of the Jordanian capital, Amman.
</P>
<P>
   The report did not say when the drugs were seized or where the
vehicle was headed.
</P>
<P>
   Jordan lies on a trafficking route for drugs from Turkey,
Lebanon and Syria that are bound for Saudi Arabia and other Gulf
states.
</P>
</TEXT>
