<HEADLINE> Cosby 'Dad' Remains Hospitalized  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Earle Hyman, who played Bill Cosby's father on
''The Cosby Show,'' remained hospitalized Saturday, one day after
he collapsed on stage.
</P>
<P>
   Hyman, 73, was acting in Edward Albee's ''The Play About the
Baby,'' when he fell to the floor about 10 minutes into the
performance Friday night. He maintained consciousness, said Paul
Tetreault, the theater's managing director.
</P>
<P>
   The actor was taken to Memorial Hermann Hospital and was in good
condition Saturday. He was to undergo tests, a hospital spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
   Tetreault said Hyman had not reported feeling ill during
rehearsals or before the performance.
</P>
<P>
   Friday night's audience included about 40 physicians. When a
request was made for a doctor in the house, four immediately came
on stage, where Albee joined them, Tetreault said. The performance
was canceled.
</P>
