<HEADLINE> Wrong Castle on Prince's Stamp  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERSEY, Channel Islands (AP) -- Postal chiefs were red-faced
Saturday after admitting they put the wrong Welsh castle on their
stamp commemorating Prince William's 18th birthday.
</P>
<P>
   The stamp, one of four to be issued by Jersey Post, was supposed
to show Caernarfon Castle in north Wales, where Prince Charles'
investiture as Prince of Wales was held. The graphic designer
mistakenly used an illustration of nearby Beaumaris Castle.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are obviously embarrassed because our publicity material
says the stamp shows Caernarfon Castle, '' said Adress Valentine,
philatelic manager for Jersey Post.
</P>
<P>
   Jersey Post, which is due to issue the stamp June 21, received
numerous calls from Wales after a publicity photo appeared in the
local newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   ''It takes 18 months to produce these stamps so we are going
ahead with our plans,'' Valentine added.
</P>
<P>
   The stamps also show the prince skiing and playing polo.
</P>
</TEXT>
