<HEADLINE> Guatemalan Bus Crash Kills 30  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- An overcrowded bus toppled over early
Saturday, killing 30 people and injuring at least 50 in central
Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities were still rescuing people from the wreckage more
than seven hours after the 6 a.m. crash that happened just outside
Chimaltenango, a city about 60 miles west of Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
   The bus was headed to the town of San Martin Jiotepeque when the
driver lost control while taking a curve through the mountainous
region in the state of Sacatepequez. Authorities said excess weight
caused the bus to flip over onto the side of the road. The legal
capacity of the bus was 60 passengers, but it was carrying 100 at
the time of the accident.
</P>
<P>
   At least 50 people, including the driver, were taken to the
National Hospital of Chimaltenango, but local authorities said the
hospital was not equipped to handle that many patients. At least 14
people remained in critical condition.
</P>
</TEXT>
