<HEADLINE> Lineup for the Sunday TV News Shows  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:
</P>
<P>
   ABC's ''This Week'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez, IMF-World Bank
meeting, Holocaust libel case. Guests: the Rev. Joan Brown
Campbell, National Council of Churches; Sister Jeanne O'Laughlin,
president, Barry University; Miami Mayor Joseph Carollo; Gonzalez
family attorney Linda Osberg-Braun; Brent Blackwelder of Friends of
the Earth; Holocaust libel case defendant David Irving and author
Deborah Lipstadt.
</P>
<P>
   CBS' ''Face the Nation'' -- Topic: Elian Gonzalez. Guests: Jose
Garcia Pedrosa, attorney for the Miami family; and Sen. Robert
Torricelli, D-N.J.
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Meet the Press'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez, gun control,
Columbine anniversary, Campaign 2000, Wall Street future. Guests:
Rep. Jose Serrano, D-N.Y., and Jose Garcia Pedrosa, attorney for
Gonzalez relatives. Sen. Charles Schumer, D-N.Y.; Rep. Henry Hyde,
R-Ill., Judiciary Committee chairman; John Podesta, White House
chief of staff; former Presidents Carter and Ford; Ron Insana,
CNBC.
</P>
<P>
   CNN's ''Late Edition'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez, budget,
Columbine anniversary, the stock market. Guests: House Majority
Leader Dick Armey, R-Texas; White House chief of staff John
Podesta; Fernando Ramirez, chief diplomat, Cuban Interests Section;
and Spencer Eig, attorney for the Gonzalez family; and Mary
Farrell, senior investment strategist with Paine Webber Inc.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fox News Sunday'' -- Topics: The economy, inflation, IMF-World
Bank meeting, Campaign 2000. Guests: Treasury Secretary Lawrence
Summers; Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz, Reform Party presidential
candidate Pat Buchanan.
</P>
</TEXT>
