<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ripken Within One Hit of 3,000  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Cal Ripken moved within one hit of No. 3,000,
singling twice Saturday night for the Baltimore Orioles.
</P>
<P>
   Ripken singled to right field in the fourth inning and beat out
an infield hit in the fifth against Minnesota's Sean Bergman.
</P>
<P>
   Ripken is trying to become the 24th player to collect 3,000
hits.
</P>
<P>
   He entered the season nine hits shy of the mark, but was just
6-for-34 (.176) going into Saturday's game.
</P>
<P>
   Ripken grounded out in his first at-bat, then singled cleanly to
right in the fourth. In the fifth, he hit a high bouncer that third
baseman Corey Koskie fielded, but had no play on.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
