<HEADLINE> Bet on Red Wins California Derby  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, Calif. (AP) -- Bet On Red rallied in the stretch to edge
Jekyll And Hyde by a half-length Saturday in the $250,000
California Derby at Golden Gate Fields.
</P>
<P>
   Bet On Red, who is not nominated to the Kentucky Derby, ran 1[
miles in 1:48.08, and paid $10.80, $5.80 and $3. Jekyll and Hyde
returned $18.20 and $5.20, and David Copperfield paid $2.40 to
show.
</P>
<P>
   Jekyll And Hyde had a late one-length lead, but Bet On Red,
under Ron Warren Jr., moved past Dr Carson then David Copperfield
and finally caught Jekyll And Hyde just before the finish line.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I swung him to the outside, it was all him,'' Warren
said. ''He couldn't have run any better.''
</P>
<P>
   Bet On Red finished fourth earlier this year in the Golden Gate
Derby on Jan. 15, losing to New Advantage by two lengths, and also
in the Golden State Mile on Feb. 12 at Bay Meadows, losing to
Globalize by a length.
</P>
