<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-15 23:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> O's' Trombley Sees 3,000 Hit Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Baltimore relief pitcher Mike Trombley has
seen this before.
</P>
<P>
   When Cal Ripken collected his 3,000th hit in the Orioles' 6-4
victory at Minnesota on Saturday night, it was the fourth time that
Trombley witnessed the milestone.
</P>
<P>
   ''Three of my teammates have done it now,'' Trombley said after
getting his first save. ''And I threw the other one.''
</P>
<P>
   Trombley played for the Twins when teammate Paul Molitor hit No.
3,000 in 1996 and when Dave Winfield did it for Minnesota in 1993.
On June 30, 1995, Trombley gave up Eddie Murray's 3,000th hit.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've been joking with Eddie about it all week,'' Trombley said
of Baltimore's first-base coach. Murray was the first person to
greet Ripken after his historic single.
</P>
<P>
   Like Ripken, Murray and Winfield reached 3,000 at the Metrodome.
That means, Trombley was on the field each time the milestone took
place in Minnesota, and four out of the 24 times it has happened in
baseball history.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm a big baseball fan,'' Trombley said. ''I'm a fan of trivia
so it's really neat.
</P>
<P>
   ''The players have all been similar,'' he added. ''Cal was like,
the hit is nice but the moment is over and it's a team thing.
That's how he approaches the game.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-15-00 2340 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000415.0201 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-15 23:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire 1, Fusion 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Hristo Stoitchkov's goal in the 48th minute
snapped Miami goalkeeper Jeff Cassar's shutout streak at a
club-record 310 minutes as the Chicago Fire beat the Fusion 1-0 on
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Diego Gutierrez started the play, passing to Ante Razov, who
moved it on to Stoitchkov at the far post.
</P>
<P>
   Stoitchkov just missed a second goal in the 82nd minute when his
shot from the right side of the penalty box missed by inches.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago goalkeeper Zach Thornton made his first start of the
season after missing the four games because of a calf injury.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago improved to 2-3, and Miami dropped to 1-1-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
