<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-15 23:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 2, Earthquakes 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Chris Henderson and Miklos Molnar scored
goals and Tony Meola saved his shutout by blocking a free kick as
the Kansas City Wizards defeated San Jose 2-0 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson scored in the 34th minute for the Wizards (3-0-1)
after taking a long crossfield pass from Preki. Earthquakes
goalkeeper Joe Cannon got a hand on the shot, but the ball trickled
into the net.
</P>
<P>
   Molnar scored in the 79th minute. His kick hit off the left goal
post, but he got the rebound and kicked it into an empty net.
</P>
<P>
   Meola stopped a rising free kick from Richard Mulroony in the
72nd minute.
</P>
<P>
   Earthquakes midfielder Khodadad Azizi was ejected in the 74th
minute for fighting in front of the Wizards net.
</P>
</TEXT>
